cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.GT 

The paper discusses the link between online convex optimization and error backpropagation on convolutional networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and game theory (cs.GT). Given that the paper focuses on deep learning algorithms and their convergence properties, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV. The use of game-theoretic concepts and the proposal of a new approach to adaptive model selection also suggest a possible classification under cs.GT.
